-- AMSC Says China Court to Hold Additional Hearing in Sinovel Case
-- B y   W i l l   W a d e
-- 2012-12-17T14:21:56Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-12-17/amsc-says-china-court-to-hold-additional-hearing-in-sinovel-case.html
American Supeconductor Corp., a U.S.
producer of wind-turbine components, said  China ’s Supreme
People’s Court agreed to hold an additional hearing regarding
its copyright infringement case against Sinovel Wind Group Co.  AMSC, based in Devens,  Massachusetts , is pursuing multiple
suits in China seeking more than $1.2 billion in damages from
Sinovel. This case is seeking damages of $6 million, AMSC said
today in a statement.  AMSC has accused Sinovel, once its largest customer, of
violating sales contracts and stealing its technology.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Will Wade at 
 wwade4@bloomberg.net  